subSubSection.paragraph:
Desmas which can be separated in basally arranged smaller desmas (
Fig. 2H
), presumably desmas I, with more tuberculate cladi, dimensions: 240-270 × 20 µm, and peripherally arranged more robust desmas (
Fig. 2G
), presumably desmas II, dimensions cladome: 200- 310 × 30-45 µm. They are not clearly separated morphologically and the larger desmas lack a distinct rhabdome. Monactinal spicules are styles and rhabdostyles, variable in form, size and curvature, the smaller sizes tend to be rhabdostyles, dimensions: 224-1000 × 14-31 µm.
